Text.Value: Wave politely.
With pleasure, my Queen.
Do this, and I will cleanse you and your allies. Do this -

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Vlaakith turns to Lae'zel at the end of the statement.
The player waves politely at Vlaakith.

Text.Value: - eliminate them and enter the Prism yourself. See that protocol is done.
Do what you deem right. I plan to do the same.
These attendants you keep - you taught them well. My child. My Lae'zel.
Can you not strike down your own foes? You command less than a thimbleful of Lady Shar's power.
Can't you kill them yourself? I thought 'gods' were all-powerful.
Your utility is proven. But your heroism is yet to be witnessed.
Choose. But know this: the cost of refusal is great.

EditorData.logicalname: Inquisitor is dead, Laezel is convinced

Text.Value: I was ordered to protect the artefact, not any stowaways it contains. I will do as you wish.
I will do as you wish.
I didn't take the weapon from you, but I am returning it.
They are an agent of the Grand Design. Sent to sabotage the Astral Prism - our last defence against the return of the Illithid Empire.
Kneel.
Who exactly are you?
Use this to enter the Prism, or deny me. The choice, as ever, is yours.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Vlaakith turns to player and looms over them instead.

Text.Value: I will cleanse it for you, my Queen. Tell me how.
A test, then, to see if you are as capable as you profess to be.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Vlaakith returns to her full posture.

Text.Value: So - it is found.

EditorData.SFXTags: [KC] Vlaakith's voice echoing through the room. The voice is disembodied and being heard pre-hologram.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player kneels, head bowed, solemn, appropriate. Vlaakith offers something resembling a smile, and gestures for the player to rise. Everyone present rises.

Text.Value: Vlaakith's eyes see beyond the planes. We cannot hide.

EditorData.logicalname: Inquisitor is dead, Laezel is convinced

Text.Value: Yes. I will enter the Prism and kill the occupant.
But know this: my wrath is carried with each of my faithful. It will find you.

EditorData.stateContext: Vlaakith's image is replaced by an image of the artefact in the planecaster.

Text.Value: YOU WISH TO SEE GODHOOD?
You have ventured far from your kind's comforts to serve us.
I expected little of istik education, but here we kneel before our Queen.
Kill them.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: With a close of her fist, the artefact hologram is shattered in mid-air in a burst of astral flare.
EditorData.SFXTags: [KC] The hologram of the artefact shatters into an astral flare as vlaakith closes her fist
EditorData.VFXTags: [KC] The hologram of the artefact shatters into an astral flare as vlaakith closes her fist

Text.Value: Follow my lead. You need to trust me, whatever comes next.
Ba na'zin. Our each step, with purpose.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Vlaakith and the hologram disappear after Lae'zel's response.

Text.Value: Not merely great, Lae'zel. Eternal.
You seek purity. I may yet grant it.
Your kind's stoic endurance will be a boon to our cause.
Stay standing, exactly as you are.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The image of Vlaakith flickers away within the planecaster, replaced by an image of the artefact suspended above the device.
EditorData.VFXTags: [KC] Vlaakith flickers and is replaced by a hologram of the artefact

Text.Value: You must accept. Refuse, and you will know my fury.

EditorData.logicalname: Inquisitor is alive, Laezel is not convinced

Text.Value: Descendant of noble dragons - you honour us with your allyship.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lae'zel grimaces in anger, but remains silent

Text.Value: No. I am not your servant to be commanded on whim.
No. I am not doing the githyanki queen's bidding.
Inquisitor W'wargaz was potent. We are impressed.

EditorData.SFXTags: [KC] Vlaakith's voice echoing through the room. The voice is disembodied and being heard pre-hologram.

Text.Value: Use the planecaster's power to enter the artefact.
It is my greatest honour to obey.
You know where my fealty lies. You have always known.
Very well - my trust is yours. But it is fragile. Break it, and be broken.
Your kind's heritage is long and storied. It is an honour to be served by one so noble.
Autonomy begets consequence.
All we've seen, all we've done, and you would abandon me?
I will wait here. Turn your back, and you will feel my blade against it.

EditorData.logicalname: Inquisitor is alive, Laezel is not convinced

Text.Value: There is someone inside. Their mind is warped, broken - a blight.
My child. You walk on the path of ascension.
You are permitted to look upon me. You are invited to kneel.
Your choice of allies is most vexing. They do not become you. Lae'zel.
W'wargaz - see that my orders are followed. If not -

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The image of Vlaakith flickers away within the planecaster, replaced by an image of the artefact suspended above the device.
EditorData.VFXTags: [KC] Vlaakith flickers and is replaced by a hologram of the artefact

Text.Value: Ch'mar, zal'a Vlaakith. We will not waste a second.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Vlaakith and the hologram disappear after Lae'zel's response.
EditorData.NodeContext: cheh-MAR ZAL-ah VLAH-kith - Vlaakith's will above all

Text.Value: W'wargaz. They are not to leave until it is done.
Do not test her. She will be our ruin.
Ch'mar, zal'a Vlaakith. You know me.

EditorData.NodeContext: cheh-MAR ZAL-ah VLAH-kith - Vlaakith's will above all

Text.Value: - and ascend.
Vlaakith gha'g shkath zai!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The Inquisitor kneels before Vlaakith's image, surprised to see her. All of his staff kneel also.
EditorData.NodeContext: pronounced VLAH-kith gawg shkaath ZAI (meaning 'For the honour of Vlaakith!')

Text.Value: Be wary of the creature's lying tongue. Cut it out, if you must.
Vlaakith has spoken. Do not leave this room except to enter the Prism. Turn your back on me, and you will feel my blade against it.
Extend your fealty one step further, and you will be rewarded beyond your mortal reckoning.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Vlaakith returns to her full posture.

Text.Value: I cannot allow that. I have a sacred mission; the artefact - the prism - is key.
I can't do that. The person inside protects me from the Absolute.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Vlaakith gains her composure and motions everyone to rise. Everyone present rises.

Text.Value: Istik. You bear that which is ours. But are you friend, or are you thief?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Vlaakith, unfazed in the least, motions everyone present to rise.l Everyone rises.

Text.Value: I spoke too hastily - please forgive me.
Did your crche teach you nothing?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: The Inquisitor hisses at the player while kneeling.

Text.Value: Obey, my child, and be forgiven.
Obey, and be forgiven.
That 'weapon' you carry - the Astral Prism - it is corrupted.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Vlaakith summons a floating hologram of the artefact and psionically spins it, toying with it.
EditorData.SFXTags: Magical swoooming and whooshes from holo-Vlaakith playing with holo-artefact
EditorData.VFXTags: [KC] Vlaakith summons a floating hologram of the artefact

Text.Value: You are being LIED TO.
Who... am... I?

EditorData.NodeContext: her facade splinters a little, letting her mad, immortal rage take over

Text.Value: BLASPHEMING TONGUE.
I WILL BE OBEYED!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The room rumbles, the gith (and inquisitor) in here look terrified
EditorData.NodeContext: she loses herself a bit in rage here,

Text.Value: I am Vlaakith. Undying Queen of the noble githyanki. God Regent of the Six Arms of Tu'narath.

EditorData.NodeContext: anger should build rhythmically here, each consonant semi-spat in rage

Text.Value: Ascension? My queen. An honour gained, a burden borne.
Your kind will go far for glory. As you have shown by being here.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Vlaakith looks the player over, and gives a ghastly, frightening smile.

Text.Value: Perhaps I misheard. You would not speak ill of a god. Would you?

EditorData.NodeContext: again, she's close to losing it a bit here, "would you" said with max venom

Text.Value: Tsk'va. Do not defy our queen!
Tsk'va. Do not defy my queen!

EditorData.NodeContext: Lae'zel panicked and angry that you have spoken against the queen to her face

Text.Value: Extend your fealty one step further, and you will be rewarded beyond your mortal reckoning.
An unexpected servant. Your will is strong.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [REUSE] HUM_M_Rig_DFLT_CINE_Step_Back_StandR_01 > player steps back when Vlaakith looms over
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Vlaakith looms in to face Lae'zel at their eye level.

Text.Value: My Queen - shkath zai!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lae'zel kneels

Text.Value: No. In fact, maybe I'll free the one inside.
I'm the hero who found your weapon.
The Deathless Queen has spoken. You will obey.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to player
Vlaakith disappears

Text.Value: Neither. It is mine, to deliver to Lady Shar.
Neither. It is mine by rights.
No. It is not 'yours'. To own something is to know it.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Vlaakith returns to her full posture.

Text.Value: Hshar'lak! You would stand against me?
I am at your command, my Queen. The artefact is yours.
Your kind is not known for trusting strangers. Quite rightly. Yet here you are.
Nonsense. She is a false god. My Lady Shar is only one worthy of respect.
I just think a real god could kill whoever she wants.
Come - we must enter the Prism. Its secrets are finally ours to know.
If you're a god, do it yourself.
The god-queen of my people cannot kill someone herself?
I Wish you to end.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: at the word "wish", Vlaakith invokes the most powerful, reality-bending magic of the multiverse. The Wish. her image shakes, as does the room around the players. we cut to gameplay, and they die .

EditorData.VFXTags: [KC] The room begins to shake as Vlaakith's image distorts

Text.Value: As you say, my Queen.
As long as they live, the Prism is compromised.
I will wait here, and you will not leave this room except to enter the Prism. Turn your back on me, and you will feel my blade against it.

EditorData.logicalname: Inquisitor is alive, Laezel is not convinced

Text.Value: You will not leave this room until it is done.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
The planecaster vibrates, shaking the ground around it. 
Flares of light curl up in its centre and grow to full form. 
Vlaakith appears, awesome and terrible, at least twice the size of any human, a hologram in a haze of astral flares.
EditorData.SFXTags: Magical booms and swooshes [KC] The planecaster vibrates with energy and a hologram of Vlaakith forms
EditorData.VFXTags: [KC] Flares of light curl up from the planecaster to form a Hologram of vlaakith.

Text.Value: Urlon of K'liir speaks most highly. As did Al'chaia before him.
Child of Gith. You carry what is mine. Do I call you loyal servant - or thief?

EditorData.NodeContext: Yank = child. YAHNK to avoid sounding like she's calling the player an American

Text.Value: Kneel before Vlaakith, your queen.
To refuse Vlaakith is to refuse me. You will do as she asks. Or I will be her wrath.

Synopsis: Vlaaktih appears as a hologram and Laezel meets her for the first time. Avatar can decide if she accepts her orders to kill the prisoner or refuse. In both cases, the planecaster is activated.If you refuse, Vlaakith orders the inquisitor if alive to kill you if you try to exit the room or theatens to hunt you down if he's already dead. If Laezel is not yet convinced to side with the player, they have a chance to do it here if they refuse.
